        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "The irrational number "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "e"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is also known as Euler's number.  It is\napproximately 2.718281, and is the base of the natural logarithm,\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "ln"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " (this means that, if "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "x = \\ln y = \\log_e y"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ",\nthen "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "e^x = y"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ". For real input, "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "exp(x)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " is always positive."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "For complex arguments, "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "x = a + ib"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", we can write\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "e^x = e^a e^{ib}"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ".  The first term, "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "e^a"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", is already\nknown (it is the real argument, described above).  The second term,\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "e^{ib}"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", is "
              },
              {
                "kind": "math",
                "latex": "\\cos b + i \\sin b"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", a function with\nmagnitude 1 and a periodic phase."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "raw_kind": "footnote",
            "raw_text": "1\n\nWikipedia, \"Exponential function\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponential_function",
            "type": "raw_block"
